article.headline: Boise State 55, Fresno State 44
article.story: FRESNO, Calif. (AP) -- Coby Karl scored 12 points as Boise State limited Fresno State to a season-low point total in a 55-44 victory Saturday night. Booker Nabors added 11 points and Aaron Haynes 10 for Boise State (15-8, 7-6 Western Athletic Conference). Shantay Legans scored a game-high 18 points with six rebounds and six assists for Fresno State (11-11, 7-6), which shot only 33.3 percent from the field. Dreike Bouldin added a career-high 13 points and 10 rebounds for the Bulldogs. Boise State led 22-20 at the half, but broke the game open with an 18-4 scoring run to start the second half, capped by Josh Bates' steal and layup that gave the Broncos a 40-24 lead with 11:24 to play. Despite persistent fouling, Fresno State got no closer than seven points the rest of the way. Boise State was 16-of-21 from the free-throw line. Fresno State, which has lost four of its last five, went to the line only 10 times, hitting 8. Both teams were short-handed. Fresno State played without suspended starters Renaldo Major, Jonathan Woods and Terry Pettis. Boise State was missing leading scorer Jermaine Blackburn with a shoulder injury.
